equation: if Coil.eps_nominal > 0.0 and Coil.eps_nominal < 1.0 then Buildings.Fluid.HeatExchangers.BaseClasses.ntu_epsilonZ(Coil.eps_nominal, Coil.Z_nominal, Integer(Coil.flowRegime_nominal)) else 0.0

assert(flow_sink_air.p_in_internal > 50000.0 and flow_sink_air.p_in_internal < 150000.0, "In Coil.flow_sink_air: The parameter value p=" + String(flow_sink_air.p_in_internal, 6, 0, true) + " is not within a realistic range for air. This is likely an error.");
assert(Coil.bal1.preDro.m_flow_turbulent > 0.0, "m_flow_turbulent must be bigger than zero.");
assert(Coil.bal2.preDro.m_flow_turbulent > 0.0, "m_flow_turbulent must be bigger than zero.");
assert(Coil.m1_flow_nominal > 0.0, "m1_flow_nominal must be positive, m1_flow_nominal = " + String(Coil.m1_flow_nominal, 6, 0, true));
assert(Coil.m2_flow_nominal > 0.0, "m2_flow_nominal must be positive, m2_flow_nominal = " + String(Coil.m2_flow_nominal, 6, 0, true));

assert(Coil.eps_nominal > 0.0 and Coil.eps_nominal < 1.0, "eps_nominal out of bounds, eps_nominal = " + String(Coil.eps_nominal, 6, 0, true) + "
  To achieve the required heat transfer rate at epsilon=0.8, set |T_a1_nominal-T_a2_nominal| = " + String(abs(1.25 * Coil.Q_flow_nominal / Coil.CMin_flow_nominal), 6, 0, true) + "
  or increase flow rates. The current parameters result in " + "
  CMin_flow_nominal = " + String(Coil.CMin_flow_nominal, 6, 0, true) + "
  CMax_flow_nominal = " + String(Coil.CMax_flow_nominal, 6, 0, true));
assert(flow_sink_water.p_in_internal > 10000.0, "In Coil.flow_sink_water: The parameter value p=" + String(flow_sink_water.p_in_internal, 6, 0, true) + " is low for water. This is likely an error.");

assert(Coil.Q_flow_nominal / (Coil.T_a1_nominal - Coil.T_a2_nominal) >= 0.0, "In Coil.Coil: Q_flow_nominal is defined with the wrong sign. By convention, a positive value describes a heat flow from Medium1 to Medium2. The parameter T_a1_nominal should then be larger than T_a2_nominal.Future version of this library might enforce this convention and throw an error.");

if noEvent(waterFlowRate > 0.001 * Coil.bal1.vol.m_flow_small) or noEvent(waterFlowRate < (-0.001) * Coil.bal1.vol.m_flow_small) then 1.0 / waterFlowRate else if noEvent(waterFlowRate < 0.5 * Coil.bal1.vol.deltaReg) and noEvent(waterFlowRate > (-0.5) * Coil.bal1.vol.deltaReg) then waterFlowRate / Coil.bal1.vol.deltaReg ^ 2.0 else Buildings.Utilities.Math.Functions.BaseClasses.smoothTransition(waterFlowRate, Coil.bal1.vol.deltaReg, Coil.bal1.vol.deltaInvReg, Coil.bal1.vol.aReg, Coil.bal1.vol.bReg, Coil.bal1.vol.cReg, Coil.bal1.vol.dReg, Coil.bal1.vol.eReg, Coil.bal1.vol.fReg)

if noEvent(airFlowRate > 0.001 * Coil.bal2.vol.m_flow_small) or noEvent(airFlowRate < (-0.001) * Coil.bal2.vol.m_flow_small) then 1.0 / airFlowRate else if noEvent(airFlowRate < 0.5 * Coil.bal2.vol.deltaReg) and noEvent(airFlowRate > (-0.5) * Coil.bal2.vol.deltaReg) then airFlowRate / Coil.bal2.vol.deltaReg ^ 2.0 else Buildings.Utilities.Math.Functions.BaseClasses.smoothTransition(airFlowRate, Coil.bal2.vol.deltaReg, Coil.bal2.vol.deltaInvReg, Coil.bal2.vol.aReg, Coil.bal2.vol.bReg, Coil.bal2.vol.cReg, Coil.bal2.vol.dReg, Coil.bal2.vol.eReg, Coil.bal2.vol.fReg)

assert(noEvent(abs(Coil.Q2_flow) < 836800.0 * max(0.001 * Coil.bal1.vol.m_flow_small, abs(waterFlowRate))), "In Coil.Coil.bal1.vol:
   The heat flow rate equals " + String(-Coil.Q2_flow, 6, 0, true) + " W and the mass flow rate equals " + String(waterFlowRate, 6, 0, true) + " kg/s,
   which results in a temperature difference " + String(abs(Coil.Q2_flow) / (4184.0 * max(0.001 * Coil.bal1.vol.m_flow_small, abs(waterFlowRate))), 6, 0, true) + " K > dTMax=" + String(200.0, 6, 0, true) + " K.
   This may indicate that energy is not conserved for small mass flow rates.
   The implementation may require prescribedHeatFlowRate = false.");

assert(noEvent(abs(Coil.Q2_flow) < 202908.0 * max(0.001 * Coil.bal2.vol.m_flow_small, abs(airFlowRate))), "In Coil.Coil.bal2.vol:
   The heat flow rate equals " + String(Coil.Q2_flow, 6, 0, true) + " W and the mass flow rate equals " + String(airFlowRate, 6, 0, true) + " kg/s,
   which results in a temperature difference " + String(abs(Coil.Q2_flow) / (1014.54 * max(0.001 * Coil.bal2.vol.m_flow_small, abs(airFlowRate))), 6, 0, true) + " K > dTMax=" + String(200.0, 6, 0, true) + " K.
   This may indicate that energy is not conserved for small mass flow rates.
   The implementation may require prescribedHeatFlowRate = false.");
assert(flow_source_air.X[1] >= 0.0 and flow_source_air.X[1] <= 1.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: 0.0 <= flow_source_air.X[1] <= 1.0, has value: " + String(flow_source_air.X[1], "g"));

assert(Coil.port_b2.Xi_outflow[1] >= 0.0 and Coil.port_b2.Xi_outflow[1] <= 1.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: 0.0 <= Coil.port_b2.Xi_outflow[1] <= 1.0, has value: " + String(Coil.port_b2.Xi_outflow[1], "g"));
assert(Coil.bal2.XiOut[1] >= 0.0 and Coil.bal2.XiOut[1] <= 1.0, "Variable violating min/max constraint: 0.0 <= Coil.bal2.XiOut[1] <= 1.0, has value: " + String(Coil.bal2.XiOut[1], "g"));
